 0885:     """
 0886:     Susceptible, Exposed, Infected, Removed (SEIR)
 0887:     The infected class has 5 groups:
 0888:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 0889:     * Is: symptomatic
 0890:     * Ih: hospitalized
 0891:     * Ic: ICU
 0892:     * Im: Mortality
 0893: 
 0894:     S  ---> E
 0895:     E  ---> Ia, Is
 0896:     Ia ---> R
 0897:     Is ---> Ih, R
 0898:     Ih ---> Ic, R
 0899:     Ic ---> Im, R
 0900: 
 0901:     Parameters
 0902:     ----------
 0903:     parameters: dict
 0904:         Contains the following keys:
 0905:             alpha: float, np.array (M,)
 0906:                 fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 0907:             beta: float
 0908:                 rate of spread of infection.
 0909:             gE: float
 0910:                 rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 0911:             gIa: float
 0912:                 rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 0913:             gIs: float
 0914:                 rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 0915:             gIh: float
 0916:                 rate of removal for hospitalised individuals.
 0917:             gIc: float
 0918:                 rate of removal for idividuals in intensive care.
 0919:             fsa: float
 0920:                 fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 0921:             fh  : float
 0922:                 fraction by which hospitalised individuals are isolated.
 0923:             sa: float, np.array (M,)
 0924:                 daily arrival of new susceptables.
 0925:                 sa is rate of additional/removal of population by birth etc
 0926:             hh: float, np.array (M,)
 0927:                 fraction hospitalised from Is
 0928:             cc: float, np.array (M,)
 0929:                 fraction sent to intensive care from hospitalised.
 0930:             mm: float, np.array (M,)
 0931:                 mortality rate in intensive care
 0932:     M: int
 0933:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 0934:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 0935:     Ni: np.array(8*M, )
 0936:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 0937: 
 0938:     Methods
 0939:     -------
 0940:     simulate
 0941:     """
 0942:     cdef:
 0943:         double gIa, gIs, gIh, gIc, fsa, fh, gE
 0944:         np.ndarray alpha, sa, hh, cc, mm
 0945:         dict params
 0946:

 1221:     method of k-stages of I
 1222:     See: Lloyd, Theoretical Population Biology 60, 59􏰈71 (2001), doi:10.1006􏰅tpbi.2001.1525.
 1223:     Parameters
 1224:     ----------
 1225:     parameters: dict
 1226:         Contains the following keys:
 1227:             alpha: float
 1228:                 fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1229:             beta: float
 1230:                 rate of spread of infection.
 1231:             gI: float
 1232:                 rate of removal from infected individuals.
 1233:             gE: float
 1234:                 rate of removal from exposed individuals.

 1236:                 number of stages of infectives.
 1237:             ke: int
 1238:                 number of stages of exposed.

 1494:     """
 1495:     Susceptible, Exposed, Activates, Infected, Removed (SEAIR)
 1496:     The infected class has 5 groups:
 1497:     * Ia: asymptomatic
 1498:     * Is: symptomatic
 1499:     * Ih: hospitalized
 1500:     * Ic: ICU
 1501:     * Im: Mortality
 1502: 
 1503:     S  ---> E
 1504:     E  ---> Ia, Is
 1505:     Ia ---> R
 1506:     Is ---> Ih, R
 1507:     Ih ---> Ic, R
 1508:     Ic ---> Im, R
 1509:     Parameters
 1510:     ----------
 1511:     parameters: dict
 1512:         Contains the following keys:
 1513:             alpha: float
 1514:                 fraction of infected who are asymptomatic.
 1515:             beta: float
 1516:                 rate of spread of infection.
 1517:             gIa: float
 1518:                 rate of removal from asymptomatic individuals.
 1519:             gIs: float
 1520:                 rate of removal from symptomatic individuals.
 1521:             fsa: float
 1522:                 fraction by which symptomatic individuals self isolate.
 1523:             gE: float
 1524:                 rate of removal from exposeds individuals.
 1525:             gA: float
 1526:                 rate of removal from activated individuals.
 1527:             gIh: float
 1528:                 rate of hospitalisation of infected individuals.
 1529:             gIc: float
 1530:                 rate hospitalised individuals are moved to intensive care.
 1531:     M: int
 1532:         Number of compartments of individual for each class.
 1533:         I.e len(contactMatrix)
 1534:     Ni: np.array(9*M, )
 1535:         Initial number in each compartment and class
 1536: 
 1537:     Methods
 1538:     -------
 1539:     simulate
 1540:     """
 1541:     cdef:
 1542:         double gE, gA, gIa, gIs, fsa, gIh, gIc, fh

 1719:             alpha: float

 1739:             tIs: float
